  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Demobilization, Disassociation, Reintegration And Reconciliation: Conflict Resolution and Peacebuilding in the Lake Chad Region (Cameroon, Chad and Niger)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This regional project will operationalize a Demobilization and Disassociation, Reintegration and Reconciliation (DDRR) program for Boko Haram fighters, associates and victims, including those caught up in related security operations. It will do so through a four pronged approach: assessment, context analysis and national planning, &#x201C;upstream&#x201D; government support, individual case management and community based reintegration and reconciliation. IOM&#x2019;s proposed DDRR approach for the Lake Chad Region for this specific project will geographically focus on Chad, Cameroon and Niger. It will integrate the various elements of the protection, prevention, stabilization, transition and peacebuilding equation to create nationally-tailored, positive &#x2018;off-ramping&#x2019; options for individuals who have separated from Boko Haram, along with community reintegration and reconciliation mechanisms, as a critical step for regional peacebuilding and restoration of social cohesion.</narrative>
  </description>
